SIMPLE: rodomontade
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rodomontade
<hw>Rod`o*mon*tade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. It.
<ets>rodomontana</ets>. See <er>Rodomont</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Vain boasting; empty bluster or vaunting; rant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I could show that the <qex>rodomontades</qex> of Almanzor are
neither so irrational nor impossible.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodomontade</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rodomontade
<hw>Rod`o*mon*tade"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To boast; to brag; to
bluster; to rant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodomontadist</ent>⟦br⟧
